Fangs					KEY:Vampire Lord ~ Fangs				TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary											DESC:You gain a Bite natural attack dealing 1d6 damage (for a Medium creature). When you deal damage with this attack, you gain temporary hit points equal to 1/2 the damage you dealt. These temporary hit points stack with themselves, up to a total equal to your maximum HP. This damage is considered Magic.		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Bite

Draining Embrace		KEY:Vampire Lord ~ Draining Embrace		TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary		DEFINE:VampireLordDrainDice|0		DESC:When you have a creature Grappled or Pinned and damage it with your Fangs natural attack, you can choose to invoke this ability. When you do, you must use the Damage action each subsequent round you succesfully maintain the grapple, automatically dealing damage equal to your Fangs attack and gaining temporary HP as you would with that attack. This ability immediately ends if the target breaks free of the grapple. When you sustain your Draining Embrace, you automatically deal a number of dice of damage equal to the number of rounds you have sustained the ability, up to a maximum of %1 dice. The number of dice increases by 1 at 7th level and every 3 levels thereafter.|VampireLordDrainDice		BONUS:VAR|VampireLordDrainDice|(1+floor(TL-1)/3)

#### Special Qualities
Thirst					KEY:Vampire Lord ~ Thirst				TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary		DEFINE:VampireLordThirstValue|0		DESC:A vampire is sustained by the blood of the living. Each sunrise, you must consume an amount of temporary HP gained from your Fangs attack equal to 10% of its maximum HP (rounded up) (currently %1). If you start the day without the requisite temporary HP, you gain the Blood-Starved special quality (see below).|VampireLordThirstValue		BONUS:VAR|VampireLordThirstValue|(ceil(HD/10))

Blood-Starved			KEY:Vampire Lord ~ Blood-Starved		TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary											DESC:If you have not consumed enough blood to sustain yourself, you suffer a -1 penalty on all d20 rolls and saves. These penalties stack with themselves every 3 days you go without accruing the requisite amount of feeding. These penalties are immediately removed once the vampire has and consumes enough temporary HP to slake its Thirst.

Frenzy					KEY:Vampire Lord ~ Frenzy				TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary											DESC:When you are below half health and take damage, you must succeed on a Will save (DC 15 + damage taken) or enter Rage as a Barbarian. You gain a +2 bonus on melee attack rolls, melee damage rolls, thrown weapon damage rolls, and Will saving throws. In addition, you take a â€“2 penalty to Armor Class.  You cannot use any Charisma-, Dexterity-, or Intelligence-based skill (except Acrobatics, Fly, Intimidate, and Ride) or any ability that requires patience or concentration (such as spellcasting). However, there are notable exceptions: You do not gain temporary HP from entering Frenzy. You can enter Frenzy even if it is Fatigued or Exhausted, but the penalties from those conditions are halved. You cannot voluntarily enter Frenzy. You cannot voluntarily end a Frenzy. You must succeed on a DC 20 Will save at the start of each turn it is Frenzied or remain Frenzied; your Will bonus from Frenzy does not apply on this save. You must attack the last creature to damage you. If you kill this creature before taking damage again, the you instead must attack the nearest creature, regardless of if it is friend or foe.

Light Sensitivity		KEY:Vampire Lord ~ Light Sensitivity	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary											DESC:You are dazzled in areas of bright sunlight or within the radius of a daylight spell.

Sunlight Weakness		KEY:Vampire Lord ~ Sunlight Weakness	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary											DESC:Each hour you are affected by your Light Sensitivity, you must succeed on a Will save (DC 15 + hours exposed) or become fatigued (ignores immunity). If you are already fatigued, you become exhausted instead. Each time you fail this save, you also gain 1 temporary negative level. You may make saves to remove these negative levels immediately upon no longer being affected by Light Sensitivity. Any negative levels that are not removed by these saves persist as normal.

